5000|$|The rubber-gaiters were {{replaced}} by a cleaned up [...] "Ceriani-style" [...] set of forks. A touted benefit was better engine cooling but, with ram air, this was a non-issue for the most part. The three separate carburetors {{were replaced}} by three <b>unitized</b> <b>rack</b> mounted carburetors with a push-pull cable arrangement. The benefits of this were less costly carburetor balancing and more accurate fuel metering. The handlebar mounted cable operated choke was gone, replaced by a lever mounted directly on the rack of carbs. The cylinder head and the ram air shroud were redesigned to cater for this new carb setup.|$|E

